    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but some people argue that the UN is basically just a tool for powerful countries to push their own agendas and that it's fundamentally broken because of the veto power in the Security Council. do historians see that as a valid criticism or is it just a fringe view?",
      "source": "evaluator"
